  "prompt": "What happened to Mt. Gox?",
  "response": "Mt. Gox was a Tokyo-based cryptocurrency exchange that was once the largest bitcoin exchange in the world, handling over 70% of all Bitcoin transactions at its peak. However, the company experienced a massive security breach in 2014, resulting in the loss of approximately 850,000 bitcoins, which were valued at around $450 million at the time. The breach led to the company filing for bankruptcy and the suspension of its operations.\n\nThe collapse of Mt. Gox had a significant impact on the cryptocurrency market and highlighted vulnerabilities in the security and regulatory oversight of cryptocurrency exchanges. Legal proceedings and efforts to compensate the affected users have been ongoing, with some partial reimbursements made, but many users are still waiting for a resolution.\n\nThe incident remains one of the most notable events in cryptocurrency history and serves as a cautionary tale about the importance of security and transparency in the digital asset industry.",
